Monte Carlo Simulation

YRandom Walk Process

set.seed(348546)
# initial graph
plot(c(0,50),c(0,0),type="l",lwd=2,ylim=c(-18,18))

# loop over draws
for(r in 1:30) {
  e <- rnorm(50) # i.i.d. standard normal shock
  y <- ts(cumsum(e)) # Random walk as cumulative sum of shocks
  lines(y, col=gray(.6)) # also display the development process
}

Var(Yt|Y0)=Var(e)*t variancet

YRandom Walk with drift 

set.seed(348546)
plot(c(0,50),c(0,100),type="l",lwd=2)

for(r in 1:30) {
  e <- rnorm(50) 
  y <- ts(cumsum(2+e)) #drift2
  lines(y, col=gray(.6))
}

set.seed(348546)

  y <- ts(cumsum(2+e))
